<br>
Anyways, has there ever been any concrete proof that different weapons have different proc rates?  I'm really not looking for an answer like &quot;Well, I had this weapon with 20 delay and this weapon with 18 delay and the 20 'seemed' to proc faster.&quot;<br>
<br>
Like...has anyone had two weapons of equal delay that have shown <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>visible</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> differences in &quot;proc rate,&quot; meaning that as with all real data, there's more than a +/- 2% variation. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koltharcawdor>Kolthar Cawdor</A> at: 3/5/03 1:23:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raaj>Raaj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 613<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/03 1:42:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2987.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon &quot;Proc rate&quot;, Bull**** or Concrete Evide</span><hr size=1> ever seen a clerics summoned hammer proc? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=331173" target="top">Raaj</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
