<br>
bloodfrenzy 16dam 20del proc:enraging blow<br>
<br>
procs 50% more per minute than<br>
<br>
Blade of Carnage 15dam 20del proc:enraging blow<br>
<br>
with identical maxxed dexterity.<br>
<br>
Weapons do have built in proc rates, and it has nothing to do with delay or haste.  Parses also show that you do not proc any more times per minute by getting haste via items or spells.<br>
<br>
A weapons proc rate is based on procs per time, and only dex affects that and even that is pretty low. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=madronedorf>MadroneDorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/03 3:31:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2987.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon &quot;Proc rate&quot;, Bull**** or Concrete Evide</span><hr size=1> From what I have seen, (But not parsed) and read...<br>
<br>
Proc rate can be adjusted, but the proc &quot;rate&quot; is usually the same for most weapons...<br>
<br>
Haste will make your proc % *LESS*, and slow will make your proc percentage *MORE*...<br>
<br>
But proc's over time is *CONSTANT*<br>
<br>
IE with a really high delay weapon, you would proc almost every single swing.<br>
<br>
You can only proc on a swing however, so being hasted, will increase the chance of proccing in the first few seconds. (I think.. mathematically this may not be true) But, being hasted will not make you proc more overall... <br>
<br>
<br>
