<br>
They measured the proc rate as a percentage of swings. They then took the proc rate and divided by the adjusted delay and basically got a constant of 0.0022 for all of the weapon setups they tested. This was a wide variety of weapons, but none that are known to proc more than is usual.<br>
<br>
My <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>guess</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is that there is a default proc rate that most weapons with a proc follow, with specific weapons being manually adjusted. The cleric hammer comes to mind, as does primal and even ye olde mistwalker. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
