<br>
It doesnt require forsite into how long fight is going to be. I *think* it would be something like this...<br>
<br>
Weapon X at 305 Dex procs is programed to proc at at aproximatly 2x Per minute...<br>
<br>
Base Delay is 60, or Ten Swings a Minute... It will proc about 1/5 swings (aproximatly)<br>
<br>
If you get 100% haste, you will swing aproximately at 30 delay (I forgot exactly how haste works, so dont yell at me if this isnt exaclty how haste works, then it will proc aproximatly 1/10 Swings...<br>
<br>
The proc percentage changes based on haste, but overall, you'll get the same amount of procs in a given time period.  (on the average) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50583">Madrone</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ~ Lord Protecter<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://members.cox.net/winterslight/">Winter's Light</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ~ Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/03 3:12:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2987.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon &quot;Proc rate&quot;, Bull**** or Concrete Evide</span><hr size=1> Actually you're more likely to get a proc when you need it if you're slowed.  Take a simplified example.  Let's say you use BoC, and it procs twice a minute (seems like a reasonable guess).  However, you really need a proc the first 10 seconds of the fight the most since that's when someone's slowing something and you need that aggro now.<br>
<br>
In 10 seconds hasted with BoC, you get 11 swings (I assume you get one free swing since your weapon has to be ready to swing the moment the mob comes in at the 0 second mark).  You should proc once per 30 swings given the ratio above.  The chance of procing is 1 - (29/30)^11 (chance of not procing at all) = 31%.<br>
<br>
Let's say now you have a 80% slow, so now in 1 minute you get 6 swings.  On average you should get 1 proc every 3 swings.  Note that now in 10 seconds, you actually get to swing twice, once on incoming and once just at the end of the 10 seconds, so the chance of procing is 1 - (2/3)^2 = 55%.  Now that even if you don't count this extra swing, you still have a 33% chance to proc.<br>
<br>
Mind you, I'm not suggesting you slow yourself so you can proc more often.  But slows actually help you proc more often since no matter how slow your weapon is or how much you're slowed, presumably you're always ready to swing when the mob is incoming, so you get an extra swing for free, but in the case of being slowed, your extra swing also has a huge increased chance of procing.  After your extra swing is up, then it averages out to be the same thing over time. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emiliaeq>EmiliaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/03 5:21:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2987.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> Proc rate IS PER WEAPON.<br>
