<br>
It's not, however.  It's just statistics.<br>
<br>
All it takes to adjust the proc over time formula is to adjust the delay. Delay is already a function of swings over time.  All you need is to say a weapon will receive an X% chance to proc for every Y amount of delay.<br>
<br>
In other words if:<br>
<br>
X = a(W) / Y where a(W) is the adjust weapon delay and Y is the modifier to decide how much proc you get then<br>
<br>
if X is set to 4% for a weapon with delay of 20, and we'll say you get 1% chance to proc for every 5 delay, then:<br>
<br>
4 = 20 / 5<br>
<br>
With 100% haste:<br>
<br>
2 = 10 / 5<br>
<br>
Presto chango you get the same procs over time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaylonn>Gaylonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/03 2:19:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2987.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/axe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re: over time..</span><hr size=1> Hehe my head hurts after reading all this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Too much math <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
